Okay, this is how I made it: Same ingredients, but slightly different order and quantities. Thanks to all whose ideas I stole! Before any other sautéing, toast pine nuts in large skillet. Remove them & sautée garlic & prosciutto in 1T of s-d tomato oil in the same pan. Add s-d tomato (small dice) and chicken (I used thin-sliced breasts cut in 1 strips) to brown w/ a little more olive oil, then add broth (1 cup) and white wine (1/2 cup) to simmer for three minutes or till chicken is just done. Meanwhile, blanch 2 cups (?) broccoli in the to-be-used-for-pasta/gnocchi water/pot. When the chickens done, stir in the basil, cheese & broccoli till heated/melted. Next time I would use more cheese; you could hardly taste the blue-ness and the sauce would be even better a little thicker. Ive avoided gnocchi for years, always finding it heavy & tasteless. But this seemed like a good recipe for it, so I gave it another try, and it was delicious! And perfect for this recipe.

